description: Barrow ended their three-game losing streak by recording a shock victory over League Two promotion-chasers Notts County.
title: Notts County 1-2 Barrow
title_page: Notts County 1-2 Barrow: Hosts drop points in promotion race - BBC Sport
maintext:
Notts County are unbeaten across their last seven Football League games against Barrow (W3 D4), though each of their three matches with the Bluebirds since returning to the EFL have finished 1-1.
Barrow have won just one of their last five away Football League games at Notts County (D2 L2), a 2-0 victory in November 1965.
Notts County have lost just one of their last 11 home league games (W7 D3) and are unbeaten in their last six (W4 D2) since a 1-2 defeat to Walsall in January.
